issue.title: feat: index.js refactoring, real-time save settings, add settings snapshots, chat room renaming and bug fixes

labels.name: enhancement
labels.description: Modify behavior of existing feature or function

labels.name: pending for author
labels.description: PR is reviewed. Waiting for the author to address the review comments.

issue.body:
This pull request introduces a major refactoring of the codebase to a component-based architecture, along with new features and several bug fixes.

Key changes include:

**Features:**
- Implement real-time settings and snapshot management:
    - Settings now save on input change with debouncing for performance.
    - New settings snapshot feature to automatically save up to 10 previous versions.
    - Improved "Cancel" button in settings to revert unsaved changes with confirmation.
- Inline Chat Room Renaming: 
    - Implemented inline editing for chat room names 
    - Includes a confirm button for explicit save and hides non-essential UI elements during rename.

**Refactoring:**
- Decompose index.js into a component-based structure:
    - UI rendering logic extracted into `src/components/`.
    - New `src/ui.js` for component rendering orchestration.
    - Event handling moved to `src/handlers/`.
    - Utilities separated into `api.js`, `storage.js`, `utils.js`.
- Pass prompts explicitly to API calls and add transparent favicons.
- Refactored API calls to use an options object for improved clarity and maintainability.
- Improved error handling and code readability in storage and utility functions.
- Used handler mapping for `handleModalInput`.

**Bug Fixes:**
- Apply font scale on page load.
- Correct errors in random first talk feature.
- Prevent message input loss on new character addition.
- Correct backup and restore logic in storage:
    - `handleBackup` now sources data from live application state to prevent data loss.
    - `handleRestore` now correctly restores `chatRooms` and `userStickers` with fallback defaults.
- Fix issues identified during refactoring:
    - UI rendering on initial load.
    - Removed call to non-existent `addKeyboardListeners`.
- Fixed a critical bug where chat room name changes were not persisted due to incorrect state mutation.
- Resolved an issue where the inline editing UI for chat rooms would not appear correctly.
- Fixed a bug causing the chat room deletion modal to remain open after completion.
- Addressed issues with character edit/delete modals not appearing immediately, ensuring correct state change detection. 
    - Prevented settings modal from resetting/collapsing during auto-save by moving snapshot creation to an explicit save action. 
    - Fixed character deletion confirmation modal not closing.
- Added a 500ms debounce to settings inputs to prevent UI lag and excessive re-rendering.
- Corrected event handling for character edit and delete buttons in the sidebar.
- Changed `checkStorageSpace` warning limit (renamed to `getLocalStorageFallbackUsage`).
- Applied fixes based on PR review.

Implement chat feature with Redux and socket integration

Added chat functionality using Redux Toolkit for state management and socket.io-client for real-time messaging. Introduced chat-related components, hooks, and types, including AddUser, ChatCard, ChatContent, and their hooks. Updated authentication and chat logic, improved UI, and refactored styles. issue.title: When switching to Fish shell the prompt shows spurious characters
issue.body:
## Bug description
When dropping to `fish` the shell prompt has spurious characters and the commands
in the history do not display correctly

## Steps to reproduce
1. Log in to an SSH server with ConnectBot
2. Dropping to fish shell
3. Prompt has spurious charactes

## Expected behavior

Uaing a Linux ssh client and dropping to fish works normally.

## Screenshots

The screenshot shows the result after typing `fish` and a few carriage returns:
![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/0f90a100-5473-45d8-8770-c13c70cad496)

## Android device

 - Device: Motorola g Power 5G
 - OS: Android 15
 - ConnectBot Version: 1.9.10-oss

## Server information

 - OS: Archlinux
 - SSH Software and Version: OpenSSH 10.0p1
 - Pubkeys used (if applicable):

## Additional context

locale is en_US.utf8 and TERM is xterm

comment.body: It looks like an VT escape sequence that `vt220.java` is not handling.

issue.title: Lock the ref impl github link to a specific commit
issue.body:
As part of WGLC, the link at the top of the Test Vectors section should be locked to a specific commit, and should also probably be moved to be a proper Informative reference.

Might as well leave this until we're pretty sure that we're done tweaking the reference implementation code, which probably means leaving it fairly late in the WGLC.

comment.body: One complication is that since we have to put the commit link into the .md and commit that, it can never point at HEAD. I think this is ok.

comment.body: ### Bug: Context Leak in Periodic GC Goroutine The periodic GC goroutine captures `ctx` from `context.Background()`. Since `ctx` is later shadowed by the signal context, the goroutine's `ctx.Done()` channel never closes, causing it to leak and run indefinitely after application shutdown.

pull_request.title: Added JetBrains InspectCode to generate a SARIF file
pull_request.body:
Integrates static code analysis using [JetBrains InspectCode](https://www.jetbrains.com/help/resharper/InspectCode.html) and publishes results as a SARIF report for processing by GitHub. It adds the ReSharper Global Tools to the build tooling, defines a new build target that runs InspectCode after compilation, and outputs a SARIF file to the artifacts directory. The test target now depends on this analysis step, ensuring code analysis runs as part of the build/test pipeline. The CI workflow uploads the generated SARIF file using the CodeQL SARIF upload action. It also updates the PackageGuard tool version.


Closes #50

issue.title: Add syntax highlighting for code blocks
issue.body:
## Overview
Add syntax highlighting support for code blocks in markdown content using a Go-based syntax highlighter.

## Tasks
- [ ] Research and select Go syntax highlighting library (likely `github.com/alecthomas/chroma`)
- [ ] Integrate syntax highlighting into markdown parser
- [ ] Support multiple programming languages
- [ ] Add line number display option
- [ ] Implement CSS theme generation for highlighting
- [ ] Add configuration options for highlighting features

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] Code blocks are syntax highlighted correctly
- [ ] Supports major programming languages (Go, JavaScript, Python, etc.)
- [ ] Line numbers display correctly when enabled
- [ ] CSS themes integrate with site templates
- [ ] Configuration allows enabling/disabling features
- [ ] Performance impact is acceptable

## Definition of Done
- [ ] Syntax highlighting has unit tests
- [ ] Performance benchmarks for highlighting
- [ ] Documentation for supported languages
- [ ] Example code blocks in test content
- [ ] Configuration documentation

## Technical Notes
- Use `github.com/alecthomas/chroma` for syntax highlighting
- Integrate with goldmark markdown parser
- Generate CSS for highlighted code
- Consider caching highlighted content

## Dependencies
- Requires #3 (markdown parser) to be completed

Estimated effort: 3-4 days

pull_request.title: SPARQL logical-not
pull_request.body: Closes #261 This PR adds `logical-not` in the same style as `logical-and` and `logical-or` and uses that for the `!` operator. While `logical-not` and `fn:not` are similar, the domain of `logical-not` is not a restriction of `fn:not` because of non-literals([Effective Boolean Value](https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql12-query/#ebv)). Other uses of `fn:not` in the document are not changed - they are apply to boolean values. The PR also corrects the NS document (#261). See also #263. *** Preview | Diff

### Where did this happen? Prod, Staging, and localhost ### Expected Behavior When signing up for Compass, no error alerts appear at any time ### Current Behavior **Localhost** Local - results in events not appearing until manually refreshing Notice the pending request, which never finishes due to the error from #603 **Once Deployed** 504 Error appears around 1 minute after the user finishes signing up **Network Tab** **Overview** ``` Request URL https:///api/sync/import-gcal Request Method POST Status Code 504 Gateway Time-out Remote Address Referrer Policy strict-origin-when-cross-origin ``` **Timing Tab** **Response for `/import-gcal`** ``` 504 Gateway Time-out

504 Gateway Time-out

nginx/1.14.2
``` ### Steps to Reproduce 0. Deploy latest from `main` to staging 1. Sign up (not sign in) for Compass with a user who has a lot of calendar data. 2. Wait for 1-2 minutes 3. See alert ### Possible Solution _No response_ ### Context Possibly related to #603. Specifically, perhaps the `/import-gcal` call is never returning due to that bug. And then when it's deployed the timeout is coming into effect. That would explain why it's not happening on localhost.

comment.body:
Findings so far:

- The GCAL_NOTIFICATION_ENDPOINT `/sync/gcal/notifications` also triggers a sync at registration time if a user account was re-registered without clearing its sync watches - This edge case will cause a race-condition with `/sync/import-gcal`
- The `/sync/import-gcal` endpoint maybe timing out without being triggered - possibly a VM problem, not associated with the running nodejs process.

pull_request.title: SPARQL logical-not
pull_request.body: Closes #261 This PR adds `logical-not` in the same style as `logical-and` and `logical-or` and uses that for the `!` operator. While `logical-not` and `fn:not` are similar, the domain of `logical-not` is not a restriction of `fn:not` because of non-literals([Effective Boolean Value](https://www.w3.org/TR/sparql12-query/#ebv)). Other uses of `fn:not` in the document are not changed - they are apply to boolean values. The PR also corrects the NS document (#261). See also #263. *** Preview | Diff

pull_request.title: feat: Add CometAPI as a model provider integration, supporting model retrieval and processing.
pull_request.body: # CometAPI Integration PR ## Context Added complete CometAPI integration to Kilo Code, providing users with access to 500+ AI models through CometAPI's unified interface. This integration includes dynamic model fetching, intelligent model filtering, and a comprehensive settings UI with debugging capabilities. ## Implementation ### Core Integration Components: 1. **Dynamic Model Fetching (`src/api/providers/fetchers/cometapi.ts`)** - Implements real-time model fetching from CometAPI's `/v1/models` endpoint - Intelligent model filtering to exclude non-text generation models (image, video, audio, TTS) - Smart context window inference based on model name patterns - Graceful fallback to static models on API failures 2. **WebView Message Handler Integration** - Updated `webviewMessageHandler.ts` to include CometAPI in router model fetching - Proper authentication and error handling for API requests 3. **UI Components and Hooks** - Enhanced `useSelectedModel` hook with CometAPI parameter support - Updated `useProviderModels` hook to handle CometAPI models - Comprehensive CometAPI settings component with debugging UI - Real-time model status monitoring and error reporting 4. **Model Filtering Strategy** - Filters out image generation models (DALL-E, Stable Diffusion, Flux, etc.) - Excludes TTS models (`tts*`), video generation (`veo*`, `runway*`, `kling_*`), audio generation (`suno*`), and MidJourney (`mj_*`) models - Maintains focus on text/code generation models only ### Key Design Decisions: - **Removed `maxTokens` field** to avoid displaying inaccurate token limits (CometAPI doesn't provide this data) - **Hybrid approach** combining dynamic API models with static fallbacks - **Extensive debugging UI** for troubleshooting API integration issues - **Smart model categorization** based on naming patterns and known model families ## Screenshots | before | after | | ------ | ----- | | No Supports for CometAPI | Now supports CometAPI with 500+ models including Claude, GPT-5, Qwen, Gemini, etc. | | Limited model selection | Filtered, curated list of text generation models only | ## How to Test 1. **Setup CometAPI Integration:** - Go to Settings ‚Üí API Providers - Select "CometAPI" from the provider dropdown - Enter your CometAPI key from https://api.cometapi.com/console/token - Optionally configure custom base URL if needed 2. **Verify Dynamic Model Loading:** - With API key configured, you should see debug information showing "‚úÖ Success" status - Debug panel should display the actual number of models fetched (typically 300-400 after filtering) - Model dropdown should populate with filtered text generation models 3. **Test Model Selection:** - Select a model from the filtered list (e.g., "claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022", "qwen3-coder", "gpt-4o-mini") - Verify the selected model appears in the bottom-left corner of the main interface - Create a new task and confirm the selected CometAPI model is used 4. **Test Error Handling:** - Try with an invalid API key - should show error status and fall back to static models - Try without network connection - should gracefully handle failures 5. **Verify Model Filtering:** - Confirm that image generation models (DALL-E, Stable Diffusion) are not visible - Verify TTS, video generation (Runway, Kling), and audio models (Suno) are filtered out - Only text/code generation models should be available for selection ## Get in Touch Available for questions about this integration. The implementation includes extensive debugging capabilities and error handling to ensure smooth user experience and easy troubleshooting.

commits.message:
VSE: Enable Pie Menu on Drag for Preview Keyframe Insert

When the "Pie Menu on Drag" is active in the preferences, pressing "I"
and then moving the mouse will open a pie menu where the user can
select which keying set to key.

Pull Request: https://projects.blender.org/blender/blender/pulls/144573

VSE: Add "Mirror" menu to preview strip menu

This PR adds a "Mirror" menu to the Strip menu within the VSE preview.
This menu is similar to the "Mirror" menu in the view3d "Object" menu.
It allows the user to access the mirror operator through a menu, rather
than via a shortcut.

Pull Request: https://projects.blender.org/blender/blender/pulls/142506

UI: Remove unused theme properties

There are many accumulated unused properties in theme. Generally, it's a mess,
lot of copy-paste errors and leftovers between editors, shared functions with no
actual use, etc. Some were just added and never used, like Pattern and Layout nodes,
which were meant to be used with Texture Nodes I believe, but it never happened.

Overall 19 properties removed:

- 3D Viewport: Edge UV Face Select
- 3D Viewport: Last Selected Point

- Dope Sheet/Timeline: Value Sliders
- Dope Sheet/Timeline: View Sliders
- Nonlinear Animation: View Sliders
- Video Sequencer: Window Sliders
- Graph Editor/Drivers: Window Sliders

- Graph Editor/Drivers: Vertex Bevel
- Graph Editor/Drivers: Vertex Group Unreferenced
- Image/UV Editor: Vertex Bevel
- Image/UV Editor: Vertex Group Unreferenced

- Image/UV Editor: Freestyle Face Mask
- Image/UV Editor: Face Retopology
- Image/UV Editor: Face Orientation Front
- Image/UV Editor: Face Orientation Back

- Node Editors: Selected Text
- Node Editors: Pattern Node
- Node Editors: Layout Node

- Video Sequencer: Draw Action

---

Details:
- Made Vertex Bevel and Vertex Group Unreferenced colors in `rna_def_userdef_theme_spaces_vertex`
optional, so that they don't appear in Graph Editor and UV Editor theme properties, where they're unused.
- Same thing in `rna_def_userdef_theme_spaces_face` for face attributes (Freestyle Mark, Retopology),
so that they don't appear in UV Editor, where they're unused. Also did same for face orientation colors,
but used different argument for them, since they could be used in future (remember seeing PR for this).
